Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
windowDeselect(25.10)                                    windowDeselect(25.10)

Name
       windowDeselect - Deselects all objects within the specified area

Syntax
       windowDeselect

       [-help]

       [<ux1>] [<uy1>] [<ux2>] [<uy2>]

       Deselects all objects within the specified area.

       Note: This command works only in GUI mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each windowDeselect parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man windowDeselect

       [<ux1>] [<uy1>] [<ux2>] [<uy2>]
              Specifies the coordinates of the window area to be deselected.

Example
       The  following  command  deselects objects that are totally enclosed by
       the area with coordinates defined as (x=10, y=200) and (x=100, y=50):

       windowDeselect 10 200 100 50

